KW  - Option pricing
KW  - Stock index options
KW  - Term structure models
KW  - Generalized method of moments
AB  - This paper tests Amin and Jarrow's (Amin and Jarrow, 1992) version of Merton's (Merton, 1973) stochastic interest rate option-pricing formula for stock options. In their model the interest rate dynamics are given by the Heath et al. (1992) term structure model. The empirical results, using data on European stock index options from the Swedish option market, show that the Amin and Jarrow model clearly outperforms the Black and Scholes (1973) model. Furthermore, the time-to-maturity bias, found in tests of the Black and Scholes model, disappears when the options are priced with the Amin and Jarrow model.
