KW  - Contract adjustments
KW  - Option pricing
AB  - When a rights issue is made on a stock, the provisions of an option contract written on that stock may be adjusted. One such adjustment is to reduce the exercise price. It is shown that this will, in general, cause a decrease in the prices of put and call options. As a result, the put-call parity theorem requires modification. The losses are quantified using a binomial model which is more complex than the standard lattice valuation model because it is necessary to model changes in the exercise price as well as the stock price.
